Description: Heavily corroded copper alloy chisel, thicker in the middle and pointing to the cutting edge, and with a thick tang of circular cross-section at the other end.
Curator's comments: One of the bronze "chisels" of "various shapes" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 28.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 28)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.75, p.184, pl.26)
